START
│
├─> 1. Include required libraries
│      - stdio.h, string.h, ctype.h
│
├─> 2. Declare functions
│      ├─ checkGuess()  → checks letter & updates display word
│      └─ checkWin()    → checks if word is fully guessed
│
├─> 3. main() starts execution
│
├─> 4. Store secret word
│      secretWord = "CLASH"
│
├─> 5. Create displayWord array
│      Example: C L A S H  →  _ _ _ _ _
│
├─> 6. Set initial lives = 6
│
├─> 7. START GAME LOOP → runs while (lives > 0)
│      │
│      ├─ Show current progress ( _ _ _ _ _ )
│      ├─ Display remaining lives
│      ├─ Take letter input from user
│      ├─ Convert letter to UPPERCASE
│      │
│      ├─ Call checkGuess(secretWord, displayWord, letter)
│      │      ├─ Loop through secret word
│      │      ├─ If letter matches → update displayWord
│      │      └─ Return 1 if found, else 0
│      │
│      ├─ If return = 0  → decrease lives, print "Wrong Guess"
│      ├─ If return = 1  → print "Correct Guess"
│      │
│      ├─ Call checkWin(displayWord)
│      │      ├─ Scan displayWord for any '_'
│      │      ├─ If '_' found → return 0 (not finished)
│      │      └─ If no '_' → return 1 (player won)
│      │
│      ├─ If return = 1 (Win)
│      │      ├─ Print "You Won!"
│      │      └─ EXIT program
│      │
│      └─ Else → loop repeats
│
├─> 8. If loop exits due to lives = 0
│      └─ Print "You Lost" + show secret word
│
└─> 9. END PROGRAM
